<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1926-08-25T10:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1926-08-25T10:00:00-05:00" n="430" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d430">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">881.00/1274: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Spain</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Hammond</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">San
                                        Sebastián</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1926-08-25T16:00:00+01:00"><hi rend="italic">August 25,
                                        1926—4 p.m.</hi></date><lb/>[Received 7:35
                            p.m.]</dateline></opener>
                        <p>62. My telegram number 60, August 25 [<hi rend="italic">15</hi>], 1 p.m.
                            Note just received from Foreign Office invites the United States
                            together with France, Great Britain and Italy, as well as all states
                            adhering to <pb facs="0827" n="731" xml:id="pg_731"/> Tangier statute,
                            to participate with Spain in a conference at Geneva September 1st to
                            examine Tangier question with special reference to Spain’s desire for
                            incorporation of International Zone with Spanish Zone. Full text of note
                            follows by telegraph. Repeated to London, Paris, and Rome.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Hammond</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>